    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Class for static polymorphism, modelled after the &quot;Curiously Recurring Template Pattern&quot; (CRTP). Used for type-safe downcasting in functions that restrict their input(s) to be classes that are derived from <ref refid="structBase" kindref="compound">Base</ref> (e.g. <ref refid="classMat" kindref="compound">Mat</ref>, <ref refid="classOp" kindref="compound">Op</ref>, <ref refid="classGlue" kindref="compound">Glue</ref>, diagview, subview). A <ref refid="structBase" kindref="compound">Base</ref> object can be converted to a <ref refid="classMat" kindref="compound">Mat</ref> object by the unwrap class. </para>    </detaileddescription>
